## Patrones de Diseño Implementados

### Container-Presenter Pattern

Separación entre componentes inteligentes (containers) y de presentación (presenters):

```typescript
// Container Component (smart)
@Component({
  selector: 'app-dashboard-container',
  template: `
    <app-dashboard-presenter
      [userData]="userData$ | async"
      (actionClick)="handleAction($event)">
    </app-dashboard-presenter>
  `
})
export class DashboardContainerComponent {
  userData$ = this.store.select(selectUserData);

  handleAction(action: string) {
    this.store.dispatch(dashboardAction({ action }));
  }
}

// Presenter Component (dumb)
@Component({
  selector: 'app-dashboard-presenter',
  template: `<div>{{ userData.name }}</div>`
})
export class DashboardPresenterComponent {
  @Input() userData: UserData;
  @Output() actionClick = new EventEmitter<string>();
}
```

### Flux Pattern con NgRx

Flujo unidireccional de datos para predictibilidad:

```
Component → Action → Effect → API → Action → Reducer → Store → Component
```

